definition.value: A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 6 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty acid anion where the last 2 carbons (omega and omega-1) form an ethyl end. Formula:C3H5O2R
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a heptaprenyl group.
A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is tetracosanoyl.
A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A polynucleotide comprised of cytidine units connected via 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages.
A benzylisoquinoline alkaloid that is berbamunine in which the  methyl group is replaced with a hydrogen on one of the tetrahydroisoquinolinol rings.

An azabicycloalkane that is 1,5-dimethyl-3-azabicyclo[3.1.0]hexane-2,4-dione in which the amino hydrogen is replaced by a 3,5-dichlorophenyl group. A fungicide widely used in horticulture as a seed dressing, pre-harvest spray or post-harvest dip for the control of various diseases.
An organic heterotetracyclic compound that acts as a partial agonist for nicotinic cholinergic receptors and is used (in the form of its tartate salt) as an aid to giving up smoking.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a nonaprenyl group.
A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 9 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 10 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is heptadecanoyl.
A sphingoid 1-phosphate that is hexadecasphing-4-enine substituted by a phospho group at position 1.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.
A tartrate salt obtained by reaction of varenicline with one equivalent of (R,R)-tartaric acid. A partial agonist for nicotinic cholinergic receptors, it is used as an aid to giving up smoking.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino group of varenicline.
A member of the class of 2-polyprenylphenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.
A member of the class of 2-polyprenylphenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as nonaprenyl.
A member of the class of 2-polyprenylphenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as decaprenyl.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatrienoyl group respectively.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycero(1-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as oleoyl; major species at pH 7.3.
A glycerophosphoglycerol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3-(all-trans-polyprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol in which the substituent at position 3 is an all-trans-heptaprenyl moiety.
A 3-(all-trans-polyprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol in which the substituent at position 3 is an all-trans-nonaprenyl moiety.
A 3-(all-trans-polyprenyl)benzene-1,2-diol in which the substituent at position 3 is an all-trans-decaprenyl moiety.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl group at both positions 1 and 2 is stearoyl.

An aminoacridine that is acridine that is substituted by amino groups at positions 3 and 6. A slow-acting bacteriostat that is effective against many Gram-positive bacteria (but ineffective against spores), its salts were formerly used for treatment of burns and infected wounds.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and stearoyl respectively.
A 2-methoxy-6-(all-trans-polyprenyl)phenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-heptaprenyl.
A 2-methoxy-6-(all-trans-polyprenyl)phenol in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-nonaprenyl.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at both positions 1 and 2 are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which both acyl groups are specified as (9E)-octadecenoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which  acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkenyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-heptaprenyl.
A 2-methoxy-6-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-nonaprenyl.
A 6-methoxy-3-methyl-2-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-heptaprenyl.
A 6-methoxy-3-methyl-2-all-trans-polyprenylhydroquinone in which the polyprenyl component is specified as all-trans-nonaprenyl.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkenyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and linoleoyl respectively.
1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and oleoyl respectively.
A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as eicosyl and linolenyl respectively.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of six isoprenoid units.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of dTDP-4-dehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which both the acyl groups specified is (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol having a side chain composed of six isoprenoid units.
A xi-progoitrin(1-) that is the conjugate base of progoitrin.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of dTDP-3,4-didehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose; major species at pH 7.3.
